items.synopsis: The Matildas meet Denmark for a spot in the quarterfinals of the FIFA Women's World Cup, after England takes on Nigeria in Brisbane. Follow live.

title.children: Sam Kerr named on bench for Matildas' World Cup knockout clash with Denmark

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Still all square with 15 minutes to go.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Half time (extra time): England 0-0 Nigeria

children.content: Still all square with 15 minutes to go.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: So, another game in this round of 16 goes to extra time. England were starting to get back into the game in that second half, but that silly mistake from Lauren James means the Lionesses are really up against it as we go another 30 minutes in Brisbane. James has been at the heart of everything England have tried so far in this game and, indeed, that they've done well this tournament. In the Men's World Cup of 1998 David Beckham was similarly sent off against Argentina in a knockout clash. This might well be this team's - and Lauren James's own personal - Beckham moment. Nigeria were slightly less effective in that half as the fatigue started to set in, but nevertheless, the Super Falcons will feel like they have a superb opportunity to become the first African team to win a knockout game at the Women's World Cup.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Full time: England 0-0 Nigeria, we go to extra time

children.content: So, another game in this round of 16 goes to extra time.

In the Men's World Cup of 1998 David Beckham was similarly sent off against Argentina in a knockout clash. This might well be this team's - and Lauren James's own personal - Beckham moment.

Nigeria were slightly less effective in that half as the fatigue started to set in, but nevertheless, the Super Falcons will feel like they have a superb opportunity to become the first African team to win a knockout game at the Women's World Cup.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well, after looking at the replay that was an easy decision to make. Things have not been going England's way in this match but she has overreacted and now put her team in deep trouble. Is this the Lionesses Beckham vs Simeone France 98 moment? A stunning lack of maturity from the (only) 21-year-old. England makes a change in response, Russo off, Chloe Kelly on.
